cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IT, cs.MM

This paper proposes a discriminative transfer learning method for general image restoration, which involves formal proximal optimization and discriminative learning. The paper focuses on image restoration, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The method also involves machine learning techniques such as transfer learning (cs.LG) and discriminative learning (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper mentions likelihood terms and priors, which are related to information theory (cs.IT) and multimedia (cs.MM).
